// USER  /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
//  This is the `user` object. Any customer on the platform is considered a
//  user. Even `nominees`, are users, just with different amount of info. This
//  is also done so that a `nominee` can be upgraded to a customer easily with
//  the pre-existing data later on.
//  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
//  flags
//  This is a collection of boolean values that gives us a sense of where the
//  users stands today. Many of the journeys depend on some of these values
//  returning as true.
//  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
//  is_owner_of
//  An array of the product ids owned by this user. It means that this user
//  started these journeys, and is in various stages of completion.
//  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
//  is_nominee_for
//  An array of the product ids owned by someone else, but has this person as
//  the nominee. Nominees will likely have only this section populated. If and
//  when they graduate to a user, other data gets populated, without breaking
//  this relationship.
//  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
//  ***-ids
//  A collection of identifiers pointing to more information about this user
//  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

